headline.main: U.S. Navy Ship Changes Course After Iran Vessel Interaction: U.S. Official
headline.print_headline: U.S. Navy Ship Changes Course After Iran Vessel Interaction: U.S. Official

lead_paragraph: Multiple fast-attack vessels from the Iranian Revolutionary Guard Corps came close to a U.S. Navy ship in the Strait of Hormuz on Saturday, forcing it to change direction, a U.S. official told Reuters on Monday.
